SIMPLE: stalemate
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stalemate
<hw>Stale"mate`</hw> <pr>(-m⟦amac⟧t`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Chess)</fld> <def>The position of the king when he can not move
without being placed in check and there is no other piece which can be
moved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stalemate</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Stalemate
<hw>Stale"mate`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <fld>(Chess)</fld> <def>To
subject to a stalemate; hence, to bring to a stand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Staleness</ent>⟦br⟧
